text: Eudonia crypsinoa is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was named by Edward Meyrick in 1884. It is endemic to New Zealand. The wingspan is 23–24 mm. The forewings are light ochreous-grey, irrorated with white. The hindwings are grey-whitish. Adults have been recorded on wing in December and January. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1884 Category:Scopariinae Category:Endemic fauna of New Zealand Category:Moths of New Zealand Category:Taxa named by Edward Meyrick
